# Tempo // OS — environment variables.
# Copy to .env.local for local dev, or add these in your Vercel project settings.
# Everything here is OPTIONAL: with no key the app runs fully on local estimators
# and Nateman's local brain. Add the key to turn on the real AI features.

# Your Anthropic API key — enables AI macros, AI training calories, and the real
# Claude-powered Nateman. Get one at https://console.anthropic.com (API Keys).
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# Optional model overrides (default for each is claude-opus-4-8).
# Haiku is a cheaper/faster choice for these light tasks:
# NUTRITION_MODEL=claude-haiku-4-5
# TRAINING_MODEL=claude-haiku-4-5
# NATEMAN_MODEL=claude-haiku-4-5

# Supabase — enables Google login + the shared friends leaderboard.
# Get these from supabase.com → your project → Settings → API. See SETUP.md.
# Both are PUBLIC (the anon key is safe to ship to the browser).
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
